==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*kar-'' (see also [[cearu]], [[cearig|ċeariġ]]).  Cognate with Old Saxon [[karon]], Old High German [[charon|charōn]], Gothic [[𐌺𐌰𐍂𐍉𐌽]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'kaɹian/

===Verb===
'''carian''' (class 2 weak)
# to [[grieve]]
# ''(intransitive)'' to [[care]], to feel concern, affection or interest

